# project-wide module identity
#
# `ModuleId` names a loaded module across the whole build. It lives in this
# leaf module, rather than on the session, so the type universe and the
# session container can both reference it without forming an import cycle.

# project-wide identifier for a loaded module, assigned by the driver as
# modules are discovered and stable for the build's lifetime
#
# Distinct from `ast.id.ModuleId`, which identifies a Module record within one
# Ast.
pub def ModuleId:   u32;
# sentinel ModuleId denoting the absence of a module
pub val MODULE_NIL: ModuleId = 0xFFFFFFFF;

# a module's build-stable identity, assigned by FQN on first sight and never
# renumbered
#
# Unlike ModuleId, which is discovery-order and reshuffles when the module
# graph changes, a StableModuleId is assigned by the session and persisted
# across rebuilds. It is the key under which cross-build-reusable artifacts
# (resolve and sema results) remap from one build's ModuleId to the next's.
# It occupies a distinct numeric space from ModuleId.
pub def StableModuleId:    u32;
# sentinel StableModuleId denoting the absence of a module
pub val STABLE_MODULE_NIL: StableModuleId = 0xFFFFFFFF;
